ee Tamahori]]\n| 432.0\n| 465.4\n| 142.0\n| 154.2\n| {{sfn|Block|Autrey Wilson|2010|pp=428\u2013429}}{{sfn|Cork|Scivally|2002|pp=300\u2013303}}<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=dieanotherday.htm |title=Die Another Day (2002) |website=[[Box Office Mojo]] |publisher=[[IMDb]]|access-date=12 October 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| ''[[Casino Royale (2006 film)|Casino Royale]]''\n| 2006\n| [[Daniel Craig]]\n| [[Martin Campbell]]\n| 594.2\n| 581.5\n| 150.0\n| 145.3\n| {{sfn|Block|Autrey Wilson|2010|pp=428\u2013429}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| ''[[Quantum of Solace]]''\n| 2008\n| [[Daniel Craig]]\n| [[Marc Forster]]\n| 586.1\n| 514.2\n| 200.0\n| 181.4\n|<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=jamesbond22.htm |title=Quantum of Solace (2008) |website=[[Box Office Mojo]] |publisher=[[IMDb]]|access-date=12 October 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| ''[[Skyfall]]''\n| 2012\n| [[Daniel Craig]]\n| [[Sam Mendes]]\n| 1108.6\n|{{formatnum:{{#expr:1108.6*(1000/{{Inflation|US|1000|2005|2012}}) round 1}}}}\n| 150.0\u2013200.0\n|{{formatnum:{{#expr:150*(1000/{{Inflation|US|1000|2005|2012}}) round 1}}}}\u2013{{formatnum:{{#expr:200*(1000/{{Inflation|US|1000|2005|2012}}) round 1}}}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=jamesbond23.htm |title=Skyfall (2012) |website=[[Box Office Mojo]] |publisher=[[IMDb]]|access-date=12 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Sizemore|first=Charles|title=Bond Investing. James Bond Investing|work=[[Forbes]]|date=10 October 2012|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/moneybuilder/2012/10/10/bond-investing-james-bond-investing|accessdate=16 November 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Smith|first=Grady|title=Box office update: 'Skyfall' blazes past $100 million internationally|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=1 November 2012|url=http://insidemovies.ew.com/2012/11/01/skyfall-smashes-100-million/|accessdate=16 November 2012}}</ref>{{inflation-fn|US|df=yes}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| ''[[Spectre (2015 film)|Spectre]]''\n| 2015\n| [[Daniel Craig]]\n| [[Sam Mendes]]\n| 880.7\n|{{formatnum:{{#expr:880.7*(1000/{{Inflation|US|1000|2005|2015}}) round 1}}}}\n| 245.0\u2013250.0{{efn|The official production budget for ''Spectre'' has been debated. Estimates range from $245\u2013250<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/box-office-preview-spectre-peanuts-836282|title=Box-Office Preview: 'Spectre' and 'Peanuts Movie' to the Rescue|author=Pamela McClintock|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=4 November 2015|accessdate=4 November 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"budget2\">{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2015/11/spectre-the-peanuts-movie-james-bond-box-office-1201610575/|title=''Spectre'' Now Targeting $73M to $74M Opening; ''The Peanuts Movie'' Cracking $40M-$45M \u2013 Updated|author=Anthony D'Alessandro|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date= 7 November 2015|accessdate=8 November 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/box-office/spectre-box-office-1201633311/|title=Box Office: ''Spectre'' Needs to Make $650 Million to Break Even|author=Brent Lang|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=4 November 2015|accessdate=8 November 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/spectre-the-peanuts-movie-give-box-office-a-welcome-boost-1447023829|title=''Spectre'', ''The Peanuts Movie'' Give Box Office a Welcome Boost|author=Ben Fritz|work=[[The Wall Street Journal]]|date=8 November 2015|accessdate=10 November 2015}}</ref> to as high as $300\u2013350&nbsp;million<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2015/10/21/why-james-bond-like-mission-impossible-is-a-bullet-proof-franchise/|title='Spectre' Doesn't Need To Top 'Skyfall' Because 'James Bond' Is A Bullet-Proof Franchise|author=Scott Mendelson|work=[[Forbes]]|date=21 October 2015|accessdate=8 November 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/spectre-movie-numbers-daniel-craig-salary-film-budget-james-bond-theme-tune-sales-1525412|title=Spectr