ner, [[Academy Award for Best Sound Editing]] at the [[85th Academy Awards]]<ref name=\"2013 Oscars\">{{cite web|url=http://www.oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/2013|title=The 85th Academy Awards (2013) Nominees and Winners|publisher=[[Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences]] (AMPAS)|accessdate=25 February 2013}}</ref> <br />Winner, [[Academy Award for Best Original Song]] at the 85th Academy Awards<ref name=\"2013 Oscars\" /><br />Winner, [[Los Angeles Film Critics Association Award for Best Cinematography|Best Cinematography Award]] at the [[Los Angeles Film Critics Association]] awards<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deadline.com/2012/12/la-film-critics-winners-2012/#more-385416|title=LA Film Critics Vote Michael Haneke's 'Amour' Best Pic, Paul Thomas Anderson Best Director For 'The Master'|date=9 December 2012|accessdate=11 December 2012}}</ref><br />Winner, [[Golden Globe Award for Best Original Song]] at the [[70th Golden Globe Awards]]<ref name=\"GG: Skyfall\"  /><br />Winner, [[BAFTA Award for Best British Film|BAFTA Award for Outstanding British Film]] at the [[66th British Academy Film Awards]]<ref name=\"BAFTA 2013\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-20955363|title=Bafta Film Awards 2013: The winners|date=10 February 2013|newspaper=[[BBC News]]|accessdate=25 February 2013}}</ref><br />Winner, [[BAFTA Award for Best Film Music]] at the 66th British Academy Film Awards<ref name =\"BAFTA 2013\" /><br />Nominated, [[Academy Award for Best Sound Mixing]] at the 85th Academy Awards<ref name=\"2013 Oscars\" /><br />Nominated, [[Academy Award for Best Cinematography]] at the 85th Academy Awards<ref name=\"2013 Oscars\" /><br />Nominated, [[Academy Award for Best Original Score]] at the 85th Academy Awards<ref name=\"2013 Oscars\" />\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Spectre''\n| Winner, [[Academy Award for Best Original Song]] at the [[88th Academy Awards]]\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color:#ccccff;\" | Non-Eon films\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Casino Royale''\n| Nominated, [[Academy Award for Best Original Song]] at the [[40th Academy Awards]]<ref>{{cite web|title=The 40th Academy Awards (1968) Nominees and Winners|url=http://www.oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/1968|publisher=[[Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences]] (AMPAS)|accessdate=27 October 2011}}</ref><br>Nominated, [[BAFTA Award for Best Costume Design|BAFTA Award for Best British Costume Direction: Colour]] at the [[21st British Academy Film Awards]]<ref name=\"bafta67\">{{cite web|url=http://awards.bafta.org/award/1968/film|title=BAFTA Awards 1967|work=BAFTA Awards Database|publisher=[[British Academy of Film and Television Arts]]|accessdate=27 September 2012}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Never Say Never Again''\n| Nominated, [[Golden Globe Award for Best Supporting Actress - Motion Picture]] at the [[41st Golden Globe Awards]] <ref>{{cite web|title=The 41st Golden Globes Winners and Nominees|url=https://www.goldenglobes.com/winners-nominees/1984?page=1|publisher=[[Hollywood Foreign Press Association]]||accessdate=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Bond girl]]\n* [[Casino Royale (Climax!)|''Casino Royale'' (''Climax!'')]], the first live-action adaptation of an Ian Fleming novel\n* [[James Bond music]]\n* [[Outline of James Bond]]\n\n==References and sources==\n===References===\n{{reflist\n| colwidth = 25em\n| refs =\n\n<ref name=\"Poliakoff\">\n{{cite journal|last=Poliakoff|first=Keith|title=License to Copyright \u2013 The Ongoing Dispute Over the Ownership of James Bond|journal=Cardozo Arts & Entertainment Law Journal|year=2000|volume= 18|pages=387\u2013436}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Shprintz:Variety\">\n{{cite news|last=Shprintz|first=Janet|title=Big Bond-holder|url=http://www.variety.com/article/VR1117492814?refCatId=13|accessdate=4 November 2011|newspaper=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|quote=Judge Rafeedie&nbsp;... found that McClory's rights in the \"Thunderball\" material had reverted to the estate of Fleming|date=29 March 1999}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Danjaq v Sony\">\n{{cite web|url=http://www.ca9.uscourts.gov/ca9/newopinions.nsf/010A5261AE3A08E788256AB4006DD2D5/$file/0055781.pdf?openelement |format=PDF |title=Danjaq et al. v. Sony Corporation et al |accessdate=27 November 2006 |author=Judge M. Margaret McKeown |date=27 August 2001 |publisher=United States Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit |page=9 |quote=in 1962&nbsp;... Danjaq teamed up with United Artists to produce Bond films. |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061004100318/http://www.ca9.uscourts.gov/ca9/newopinions.nsf/010A5261AE3A08E788256AB4006DD2D5/%24file/0055781.pdf?openelement |archivedate= 4 October 2006 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Numbers franchises\">\n{{cite web |title=Movie Franchises |work=The Numbers |publisher=Nash Information Services |url=http://www.the-numbers.com/movies/series/franchisesW.php |accessdate=3 January 2013}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"economist\">\n{{Cite news |author=The Economist online |date=11 July 2011|title=Pottering on, and on |work=[[The Economist]] |url=https://www.economist.com/blogs/dailychart/2011/07/film-franchises |accessdate=4 January 2012}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"CR: MGM\">\n{{cite web|title=Casino Royale (1967)|url=http://www.mgm.com/view/movie/342/Casino-Royale-(1967)|publisher=[[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]]|accessdate=8 September 2011}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"lost\">\n{{cite web|title=The Lost Bond|url=http://www.totalfilm.com/features/the-lost-bond|work=Total Film|publisher=[[Future Publishing]]|accessdate=13 October 2011|date=27 February 2008}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"MGM acq\">\n{{cite press release | title = Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer Inc. announces acquisition of Never Say Never Again James Bond assets | publisher = [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]]| date = 4 December 1997 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080505213137/http://mgm.mediaroom.com/index.php?s=43&item=47&printable|archivedate=5 May 2008| url = http://mgm.mediaroom.com/index.php?s=43&item=47&pri